choices.text: Craving snacks.This has resulted in forking out loads of money every few months buying snacks for comfort.I wonder if theres any way to deal with this craving ? I no longer care about weight loss with Ramadan nearing i.e fasting . So basically just the binging :) I am already following few diet advice found from this site and starting moderate exercise too(Maybe strict after Ramadan?). Thank you.I feel like I am worthy of more than Keto. Is it healthy to go the rest of my life without the high I get from Keto. Can Kettle Bell Swing really get me there in long run? Are fruits so wrong for me they can make up half my daily calorie intake? Why not carbs? Am I too fat to have sugar? Shouldn't I have sugar? Can chia seeds really be that powerful to kick my a@@ into gear? Squats? Shouldn't I be areobic? c'mon - lazy person here why work harder than I have too. Listen. I know all I need to know about Keto and what it's done for me. I lost 50 pounds. Quit being a fat ass. Goal achieved. Now what do I do? What are my options? I like to,please my wife even though I am usually empty instead of full. And I have the worst digestion of anyone I know - just ask my wife lol. Hee Rachel and Rod - you guys live an awesome life. BTW - I've been following you guys for awhile -
